devdoc.author: Brian Ludlam

ageOf(uint256).return: age = spawn timestamp of entity,  or zero if not spawned yet.

approve(address,uint256).details: caller must be: owner or owner operator.

params.to: = account address to give approval. Can't be address zero or owner.

params.name: = string name of entity, max 32 bytes
params.parentA: = id of parentA entity, or zero/null
params.parentB: = id of parentB entity, or zero/null

genesOf(uint256).return: genes - genes of entity as an array of  32 8bit gene values (0-255) each.

getEntity(uint256).return: owner = entity ownerborn = spawn timestamp of entity, parentA of entity, as uint, zero if noneparentB of entity, as uint, zero if none name of entity as a string.genes genes of entity as an array of 32 8 bit values

nameOf(uint256).return: name - name of entity as a string.

parentsOf(uint256).return: parentA and @return parentB of entity, as two uint  entity ids. Zeroes if null parents.

params.approved: = Toggle approved operator power on or off.
params.operator: = Account to give approval for operator power.

spawnCount().return: count - number of spawns ready to spawn  on current block.
